The paper deals with image processing and specifically focuses on using denoising algorithms for regularization in inverse problems. This makes it highly likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Additionally, the paper heavily relies on optimization techniques, which suggests it could also belong to the information theory (cs.IT) or machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The paper also mentions image deblurring and super-resolution problems, which are common topics in multimedia (cs.MM) and signal processing (cs.SI) sub-categories.
